### CheckPoint — Admin Users endpoints
### Requires an ADMIN account. Obtain a JWT via the login request below,
### then paste it into the @token variable.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@token = PASTE_YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_HERE

### Login to obtain a JWT (copy "accessToken" from the response into @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@checkpoint.local",
  "password": "your-password"
}

### List all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get a single user by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Edit a user (clear bio/picture, toggle profile visibility)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clearBio": true,
  "clearPicture": false,
  "isPrivate": true
}

### Ban a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/ban
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Unban a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/unban
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
